      • EditTextController

        public EditTextController(android.content.Context ctx,
                  java.lang.String name,
                  java.lang.String labelText,
                  java.lang.String placeholder,
                  boolean isRequired,
                  int inputType)
        Constructs a new instance of an edit text field.
        Parameters:
        ctx - the Android context
        name - the name of the field
        labelText - the label to display beside the field. Set to null to not show a label.
        placeholder - a placeholder text to show when the input field is empty. If null, no placeholder is displayed
        isRequired - indicates if the field is required or not
        inputType - the content type of the text box as a mask; possible values are defined by InputType. For example, to enable multi-line, enable InputType.TYPE_TEXT_FLAG_MULTI_LINE.

        Parameters:

      • isSecureEntry

        public boolean isSecureEntry()

        Returns:

      • setSecureEntry

        public void setSecureEntry(boolean isSecureEntry)
        Enables or disables secure entry for this text field. If enabled, input will be hidden from the user. Default is false.
        Parameters:
        isSecureEntry - if true, input will be hidden from the user, otherwise input will be visible.
